OL,3,CRussian captain appears in court over
OL,4,Cfatal North Sea crash
OL,6,FThe Russian captain of a container
OL,7,Fship that crashed into a US oil tanker
OL,8,Fin the North Sea has appeared in court
OL,9,Fcharged over the death of a fellow
OL,10,Fcrew member.
OL,12,FVladimir Motin, 59, was the master of
OL,13,Fthe Solong when it collided with the
OL,14,FStena Immaculate off the coast of East
OL,15,FYorkshire on 10 March.
OL,17,FSolong crewman, Philipino national
OL,18,FMark Angelo Pernia, 38, is missing
OL,19,Fpresumed dead following the incident.
